Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri The Imo State Assembly on Monday approved a budget of N332.831 billion for the 2021 fiscal year. This figure excludes the Consolidated Revenue Fund Charge of N13.3bn making it a total of N346.1bn. The passage of the budget came just four working days after it was presented by the state governor, Hope Uzodinma. He presented the budget for consideration and approval on Wednesday last week. The approval was sequel to the adoption of the report presented by the House Committee on Appropriations by a committee of the whole chaired by the Speaker, Paul Emeziem, during a special session. Out of the figure approved, N271.5bn was earmarked for capital expenditure while recurrent expenditure is to gulp N61.3bn. The office of the governor received the highest allocation for recurrent expenditure with N11.471bn while Works received the highest vote for capital expenditure with N83.09bn. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   